{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1c7abc16-14ae-46d5-945c-06d1a0e2698a","content":"Yes, you will hit **target framework compatibility issues**. MSTest v3 drops support for:\n\n- **`net5.0`** — .NET 5 is out of support; you need **net6.0+**\n- **`net462`** — minimum .NET Framework is now **net462**, so this one is fine\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — dropped; you need **net6.0+**\n\n### Summary of required changes\n\n| Current TFM | Issue | Fix |\n|---|---|---|\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped in MSTest v3 | Upgrade to `net6.0` or `net8.0` |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped in MSTest v3 | Upgrade to `net6.0` or `net8.0` |\n| `net462` | ✅ Still supported | No change needed |\n\nYou'll need to update `TargetFrameworks` to something like:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net8.0;net462</TargetFrameworks>\n```\n\nbefore upgrading the MSTest packages to v3. Would you like me to perform the full migration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2348d780-3ab8-4819-ae5e-840d3276c8a3","outputTokens":287,"requestId":"BC22:1CB4B6:20E38C2:24AF300:69FAA837"},"id":"08335c07-de12-416f-940d-58639b0023e7","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:32:29.578Z","parentId":"d2e3dbff-5680-4292-b359-d84dfd219b1d"}
